<item>
            <title>[LU-10947] conf-sanity test_116: mkfs: failed to execute mkfs.xfs: No such file or directory</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-10947</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This issue was created by maloo for sarah_lw &amp;lt;wei3.liu@intel.com&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This issue relates to the following test suite run: &lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_sets/24c8707e-472a-11e8-960d-52540065bddc&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_sets/24c8707e-472a-11e8-960d-52540065bddc&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;test_116 failed with the following error:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;mkfs temporary xfs image
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;env: SLES12 SP3 client and server&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;test log&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;
Loading modules from /usr/lib64/lustre
detected 2 online CPUs by sysfs
Force libcfs to create 2 CPU partitions
CMD: trevis-13vm12 mkdir -p /mnt/d116.conf-sanity
CMD: trevis-13vm12 touch /tmp/f116.conf-sanity-mdt0
CMD: trevis-13vm12 mkfs -t xfs -d file,size=1t,name=/tmp/f116.conf-sanity-mdt0
trevis-13vm12: mkfs: failed to execute mkfs.xfs: No such file or directory
 conf-sanity test_116: @@@@@@ FAIL: mkfs temporary xfs image

&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;VVVVVVV DO NOT REMOVE LINES BELOW, Added by Maloo for auto-association VVVVVVV&lt;br/&gt;
 conf-sanity test_116 - mkfs temporary xfs image&lt;/p&gt;</description>
